Results.ReviewText: I have drunk gold blend for at least 9 years but have now changed to Kenco due to the fact that you have changed your recipe. Until you do you have lost a loyal customer

Results.ReviewText: Have been buying Gold Blend for many years. The new packaging comes with a new taste and while the first is nice, the second is not. I don't know what Nescafe have done to it but I won't be buying it again until I know they have put it back to the rich, flavoursome version I am used to.
Results.Title: Used to be SO nice but now tastes like Sugar Puffs

Results.ReviewText: I have drank Nescafé Gold Blend for more years than I care to remember and I have always enjoyed it, until now. I purchased the new jar and thought Nescafé had done good with the revamp until I tasted it. It is bitter and why does it go like you have not added milk? Disappointed Nescafé, please give us our beloved original blend back.
Results.Title: What have you done?

ClientResponses.Response: We’re always wanting to improve the product experience for our consumers here at NESCAFÉ so it's disappointing to hear that you're not happy with the changes we've made. We've made a note of all your comments now & will be passing them to the rest of the team!

Results.ReviewText: I remember my first taste of Gold Blend in 1987 and 30 years on we are a household of 4 adults typically drinking 2 x 200g jars a week of our favourite coffee. When I bought the new shape jar I thought it was an improved design, however, I had no idea that it contained a different product. The new Gold Blend is quite frankly awful. Some of the non-soluble particles remain in suspension and leave a fine grittiness in the mouth with a bitter taste. It does not replicate 'barista coffee'; it is more like the last cup from a cafetiere. We so much enjoyed the original Gold Blend that we would never have considered changing brands but after reluctantly working our way through half a jar of the new stuff, I have gone out and bought 2 competitors products to try. They are both as good as original Gold Blend, perhaps even better. I can't even start to understand Nescafe's marketing strategy but you have lost sales of about 100 jars a year from this household.
Results.Title: Unpleasant grittiness with bitter taste

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, we really appreciate you taking the time & letting us know your thoughts on the changes we've made! It's disappointing to hear that you're not happy with them but we really value your comments.

Results.ReviewText: Have been drinking Gold Blend for more years than I care to remember, the recent change to what I though was only the jar and label are entirely unwelcome.
